task.summary: Version control xml file added from Intellij
Disposing JFrame when losing focus on the settingmenu.
Abstract Class made for Settings menu's. Added logo's for jenkins and SSH.
Added click to add functionality, created a model which also enholds the settingsmenu and service which can be called via the model. Made some structure naming conventions and design patterns.
Cleaned commentedCode and created JButton for creation of Jenkins Model to be drawn on the workspace.
Added Listeners and created form functionality with JPanel.

Refactored names of menus which are in fact forms. Created Workspace functionality with a service included. Added a MouseListener for acting on the workspace canvas. Models which are created by the form can now be adjusted with a form. Added an model for serviceCredentials.
Added runnable jar compressed with dependencies which runs with a minimum of JRE 8.
The port of an host has an seperate field, the service painted on the workspace automatically have space between them for a better overview. A socket is used for checking the host is reachable.
Service forms are now table like arranged, added two buttons with image for run workspace and settings button.
Created binary of the latest commit.
Jenkins service linked to JenkinsModel, jenkins form linked to jenkinsmodel. The jenkinsmodel acts as a proixy object for the jenkins information and data. Cleanup code.
